cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with conversational intent understanding for passengers in autonomous vehicles, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. Additionally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the development of a contextual dialogue system for handling vehicle-passenger interactions. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, since the paper deals with autonomous vehicles, cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category.
